subject: ho604e1e0c5lsjf
previous_experience: not sure when but in some previous study or studies and in discussions of philosophy and moral psychology
final_comments: I think their choice was unwise and likely to damage their relationship, but these prudential judgments are not the same as moral judgments. I would also add that I was not satisfied with the range of options given. Specifically, I think this choice was closer to being not wrong than wrong, but I think it was irresponsible in ways that might have moral implications without being enough to define the act as wrong. For instance, I think they each should have anticipated that the other might be harmed in the future by their decision even while consenting in the moment. Also, I don't know how carefully they thought about the likely future effect of this act, so I can't say for sure that it was wrong or irresponsible. The scenario is very simplified, too much so to really understand their state of mind well.
